                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 337.11/268</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-12T19:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">March, 12, 1917, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>American administrator of Punta Alegra Sugar Mills, Camaguey, belong to Atkins,
                    together with Lieutenant of Federal forces, went to meet rebel leader to receive
                    his surrender. Neither have returned. Atkins says rebels [omission] as ransom.
                    Have notified naval commander and Cuban Government has sent two detachments
                    cavalry.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
